In summary, ECC pays the bank, West LB directly in three installments under=20
an off-balance sheet lease financing arrangement.  The first installment of=20
$US 9MM was made Dec. 1/99.  The next installment is due Feb. 1/00 of $US=20
8MM, and the third installment is due roughly March 31/00 of $US 8MM. The=20
"drag" on the financing is that West LB through whom ENA structures its=20
off-balance sheet turbine financings is not a Canadian resident for tax=20
purposes, and therefore is not tax efficient to ECC in that there is a 15%=20
